docs.abstract: Mr. Buttigieg, the mayor of South Bend, Ind., attended a heated protest following the shooting of a black man by the police there.
docs.snippet: Mr. Buttigieg, the mayor of South Bend, Ind., attended a heated protest following the shooting of a black man by the police there.
docs.lead_paragraph: SOUTH BEND, Ind. — While his 2020 rivals mingled with large friendly crowds at a Democratic fish fry in South Carolina Friday night, Mayor Pete Buttigieg found himself somewhere very different, wading into an emotional knot of protesters at the South Bend Police Department, some of whom cursed him, interrupted him and shouted a list of demands through a megaphone feet from his face.

headline.main: Buttigieg Leaves Campaign Trail After Fatal Shooting. Reality Rears Its Head.
headline.print_headline: Buttigieg Skips Event Only to Face Ire at Protest

docs.abstract: The program would ensure that renters would not spend more than 30 percent of their income on rent, Mr. Booker said.
docs.snippet: The program would ensure that renters would not spend more than 30 percent of their income on rent, Mr. Booker said.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey on Wednesday unveiled a plan to tackle affordable housing that would provide a tax credit for renters to ensure they would not spend more than 30 percent of their income on rent — a sweeping new entitlement program that his campaign estimated would reach 57 million Americans, including 17 million children.

headline.main: Cory Booker’s Housing Plan Offers Tax Credit to Millions of Renters
headline.print_headline: On Day of Policy Plans, Booker Adds His: A Renter Tax Credit

byline.original: By Shane Goldmacher and Conor Dougherty

docs.lead_paragraph: Amy McGrath, a retired Marine lieutenant colonel and combat pilot who is seeking to unseat Senator Mitch McConnell in 2020, raised $2.5 million in the first 24 hours of her campaign, her campaign manager said Wednesday.

docs.lead_paragraph: After spending two weeks sparring with his presidential primary opponents, Joseph R. Biden Jr. sought once more to rise above the Democratic fray on Thursday, delivering a sweeping foreign policy address that denounced President Trump as incapable of global leadership and called for a new commitment to multilateral diplomacy.

docs.abstract: The shooting of a black resident by a white police officer has revived scrutiny of Mr. Buttigieg’s sometimes strained relationships with the black community.
docs.snippet: The shooting of a black resident by a white police officer has revived scrutiny of Mr. Buttigieg’s sometimes strained relationships with the black community.
docs.lead_paragraph: SOUTH BEND, Ind. — Mayor Pete Buttigieg remained in South Bend, Ind., on Tuesday to confront a local crisis involving the fatal shooting of a black resident by a white police officer, skipping scheduled campaign appearances in Hollywood.

headline.main: Buttigieg Facing Test of Leadership After Shooting in South Bend

docs.abstract: In New Hampshire, the former vice president went after some of his rivals, with criticism that Bernie Sanders called “totally absurd.”
docs.snippet: In New Hampshire, the former vice president went after some of his rivals, with criticism that Bernie Sanders called “totally absurd.”
docs.lead_paragraph: ATKINSON, N.H. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. spent the first months of his presidential campaign largely ignoring his nearly two dozen rivals, seeking to stay above the Democratic fray as he cast himself as an unapologetic pragmatist who could beat President Trump in a general election.

headline.main: Joe Biden Decides He Doesn’t Need to Stay Above the Fray After All
headline.print_headline: After Months Above Fray, Biden Decides to Jump In

docs.abstract: Ms. Hallquist, a Vermont Democrat, made history Tuesday night by becoming the first transgender nominee for governor from either major party. She spoke to The Times the next morning.
docs.snippet: Ms. Hallquist, a Vermont Democrat, made history Tuesday night by becoming the first transgender nominee for governor from either major party. She spoke to The Times the next morning.
docs.lead_paragraph: Christine Hallquist, the former chief executive of an electric utility company, made history on Tuesday when she beat three other candidates in Vermont’s Democratic primary to become the first transgender person to be nominated for a governorship by a major party.

headline.main: Christine Hallquist on Her Primary Victory: ‘It Gives the Transgender Community Hope’
headline.print_headline: Primary Victory in Vermont ‘Gives the Transgender Community Hope’
